<L>__{interior exterior 1st apartment day}
<A>__{szpilman's pov the street. in the street below, he sees ss men escorting two prisoners and shoving into a car. the car speeds off. the street is empty.}
<L>__{interior 1st apartment dusk}
<A>__{snow. howling wind. szpilman lies on the divan. he is cold, unshaven, hair filthy and long. he manages to rise.}
<B>__{the small kitchen.}
<A>__{a mess. szpilman goes into the kitchen. from a bread tin he takes a small, flat greaseproof paper parcel and unwraps it. a slice of bread, stale and mouldy. he tries to bite it but can't. he finds a knife and tries to chop a piece off the bread but knocks the bread tin, which falls to the floor with a clatter. he continues to try to cut the bread, when there's a loud hammering on the front door. szpilman stiffens.}
<B>__{the living room.}
<A>__{the hammering continues as szpilman stumbles into the room, looks around, confused, not knowing what to do. from the other side of the door female voices, words indistinct, and then:}
<C>__{kitty's voice}
<D>__{open this door at once, or we'll call the police!}
<A>__{he is galvanised into action, puts on a crumpled jacket, grabs his tattered coat and scarf, collects up a few of his things, stuffs them into a paper bag. the hammering stops. szpilman cautiously approaches the door, listens, then opens it quietly and slips out.}
